  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Traditionally, the performance of ML models is established through \"testing and validation.\"",
    "But one must question if this standard method of testing is adequate for crucial applications such as power system protection and control.",
    "Consider an ML model that demonstrates an accuracy of 99% during testing.",
    "While this might seem commendable in many fields (Wu and Chen, 2016; Islam et al., 2018) in power system applications, a 1% error margin could result in severe consequences.",
    "This seemingly small percentage of error could provoke a massive system failure, emphasizing the severity of even minor inaccuracies."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "While this might seem commendable in many fields (Wu and Chen, 2016; Islam et al., 2018) in power system applications, a 1% error margin could result in severe consequences."
  ]
}